  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 79 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 54 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 840 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 55 minutes
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/family-style-creamy-chicken-pasta-bake-64dbda3f7e32e9eeac712acd
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and
preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} (two large pots for 8) of
salted water to a boil.

Drop @cream cheese{6%tablespoon}(in packets) in a small #bowl{} of warm water
to soften until ready to use. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel,
and finely dice @yellow onion{1%unit}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}.

Generously coat a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} (two 9-by-13-inch baking dishes
for 8 servings) with @nonstick cooking spray{} and set aside.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{12%ounce} to #pot{} (for 8 servings,
divide between two large pots or cook in batches). Cook, stirring occasionally,
~{6%minutes}.

Add broccoli. Cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is bright green and
pasta is al dente, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain pasta and broccoli.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over high
heat. Add @chopped chicken breast{20%ounce}*, onion, and garlic in a single
layer; season with @fry seasoning{2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and onion is
tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches to prevent
> overcrowding, adding a drizzle of oil between batches.

In a large bowl, whisk together @cream sauce base{8%ounce}, @white cheddar
cheese{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit}, and cream cheese (work in
batches or use two large bowls for 8 servings).

Add drained pasta and broccoli, chicken, and ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water
(1 cup for 8) to bowl with sauce and stir to thoroughly coat.

Transfer pasta mixture to prepared #baking dish{} (divide between two baking
dishes for 8).

Cover baking dish tightly with foil, then place on top of a foil-lined
#baking sheet{} (two baking sheets for 8 servings).

> The sheet will help protect your oven from any sauce that may bubble over!

Bake on middle rack (top and middle racks for 8) until bubbly, ~{30%minutes}.

Stir pasta bake to evenly distribute sauce. Let rest at least ~{5%minutes} before
serving.

Divide pasta bake between plates or serve family style directly from dish.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.